      <p align="center"><font size="4"><b>Assignment 1</b></font></p>
	  
	  <div align="center"><b>UPPER STOREY EXTENSION</b>
<br>
        (Lot 22) </div><br>
     <b>Instructions to Candidates:</b><div style="line-height:8px"><br></div>
1.        Sheet size - preprinted A3 tracing paper.
<div style="line-height:4px"><br></div>
2.        Candidates are to produce the required plan, elevation and section for Lot 22, to the scales nominated, using the supplied dimensioned plan, and elevation.<div style="line-height:4px"><br></div>
3.        All necessary construction dimensions, lettering, notes, etc., are to be included on the drawings. Read 'ARCHITECTURAL DRAWING' pages 76, 77 & 78.<div style="line-height:4px"><br></div>
4.        The original work in ink on tracing paper PLUS A3 size photocopies are to be submitted for marking at the beginning of class in WEEK 7. Penalties apply for late submission.<div style="line-height:4px"><br></div>
Drawing Information and Requirements: <div style="line-height:6px"><br>
      </div>
      <b>Sheet 1 - Plan</b><br>
At scale 1:100 draw the ground floor roof and upper floor plan, the position of the upper floor over the house level is shown on the attached upper floor extension sketch. Dimension the position of the upper floor plan in relation to the ground floor external walls and, dimension the upper floor plan with all necessary construction dimensions and information.<div style="line-height:6px"><br></div>
      <b>Sheet 2 - Elevations</b><br>
At scale 1:100 draw the front (1) and side (2) elevation for the house with the extension. Window sizes and locations in the extension are at the candidates' discretion. Information which may assist you is given on the following page under 'Construction Information'.<div style="line-height:6px"><br></div>
      <b>Sheet 3 - Section</b><br>
At 1:50 scale draw a section through the house and extension on line 01. Section to be from outside the gutter on the LHS, to 1.5m outside of the extension wall on the RHS.<div style="line-height:12px"><br></div>
  
  <div align=right> 
        <p>[ <a href="#top">top of page</a> ]</p>
      </div>
	  
	  
	 <a name="sect1"> <b>Construction Information</b></a>
<div style="line-height:6px"><br></div>
     
        o   Existing buildings' footing system is 450 x 250 separate edge beam perimeter concrete strip, with a 100 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;thick slab on ground floor slab, thickened under internal walls as well as external walls in accordance with &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;BCA figure 3.2.5.5.
<br>
        o    200 UB's at position shown on the Upper Floor Extension Sketch. The bottom of the UB's is 11 mm &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;above the top of the ceiling joists.
<br>
        o   Upper floor joists 240 x 35 F.5 seasoned softwood, spaced at 450mm centres running across the &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;extension.
<br>
        o    Sheet platform floor 19mm particleboard to dry area floor, 18mm compressed sheet to wet area.
o   Wall &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;frame materials 90 x 35 F.5, seasoned softwood studs at 450 centres, top plate 90 x 45, noggins and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;bottom plates 90 x 35.
<br>
        o   Roof frame is pine F.5 trusses at 600 max. centres; truss design as in CONSTRUCTION 2 text book, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;pages 83-87 and NOTES.
<br>
        o   Upper floor eaves overhang boxed, and lined with 4.5mm 'Hardiflex' then finished with metal fascia and &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;gutter.
<br>
        o   Roof covering materials, eaves overhang and pitch to match ground floor existing.
o   Upper floor cladding &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;to be Hardie's 'Prime Line' weather boards.
<br>
        o   Upper floor lining to be 'Gyprock' 10mm thick sheets (to walls and ceilings) with 75mm cove cornice.
o    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Extension wall height 2700mm.
<br>
        o   Window sizes and positions in the extension walls are at the candidate's discretion but must be meet BCA &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;requirements and, be from a stated fabricator's catalogue.
<br>
        o    Step Going: 275mm
<br>
        o    Stair width between strings: 1010mm
<br>
        o    Stair strings: 240 x 45
<br>
        o   Existing ground floor walls top plate: 35 x 90 F.5 seasoned softwood
<br>
        o   Existing ground floor ceiling joists: 90 x 35 F.5 seasoned softwood
<br>
        o    Stair newel posts: 120 x 120
o    Stair treads: 45 thick
o    Stair handrail: 120x45 on edge
<br>
        o   Existing ground floor rafters: 120 x 35
<br>
        o    Roof truss top chord: 120 x 35, web members 90 x 35
<br>
        o   Roof tile battens: 50 x 25 at 320 centres approx.
<br>
        o   Roof tiles: 400 x 25
o   Eaves joists: 70x35

	 
